name: landsat-level-2-land-cover-classification-of-twin-cities-metropolitan-area-2000
notes: Raster-based land cover data set derived from 30-meter resolution Thematic Mapper satellite imagery. Classifications are divided into two levels; this is the level-2 map. The coverage consists of 12 classes including: 0-4% impervious, 5-10% impervious, 11-25% impervious, 26-50% impervious 51-75% impervious, 75-100% impervious, Cropland, Planted trees & grasses, Coniferous, Deciduous, Upland shrubland & herbaceous, Lowland shrubland & herbaceous, Water. Definitions for these classes are based on the Minnesota Land Cover Classification System (MLCCS).
